{
  "message": "fuzz: strengthen seed corpora for xattr, extent tree, htree/mmp\n\nExpand minimal seed corpora (1-2 entries each) with structured test\ninputs that exercise actual parser code paths:\n\nfuzz_xattr_parsing (was 1 seed, now 6):\n- Multi-entry with user/trusted namespaces\n- Security namespace with long value\n- Special namespace types (posix_acl_*, richacl)\n- Max suffix length boundary\n- Random entropy seed\n\nfuzz_extent_tree (was 2 seeds, now 7):\n- Valid ext4 extent leaf with magic 0xF30A\n- Depth-1 index node with entries\n- Empty tree (header only)\n- Invalid magic for rejection path\n- Max entries boundary condition\n\nfuzz_ext4_htree_mmp (was 2 seeds, now 7):\n- MMP clean/fsck/active states (magic 0x004D4D50)\n- DX root minimal and deep (indirect_levels=3)\n\nThese seeds provide better initial coverage for security-critical\nparsers without adding any code changes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
